    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n4700" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἰ̄θύς</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">εῖα, ύ</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">straight;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τέτραπτο πρὸς ἰθύ οἱ</span>, ‘straight
          opposite him,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 14.403</span></i>; usually
          metaph., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">straight, right, just</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.580</span></i>; sup., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἰθύντατα</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">most fairly</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 18.508</span></i>.—As adv., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἰ̄θύς, ι&lt;&gt;̓θύ</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">straight
            at, straight for</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινός</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Il. 5.849</span></i>; also with prepositions,
          and abs., <i><span class="en">Il. 20.99</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 3.10</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἰ̄θὺς φέρειν, μάχεσθαι, φρονεῖν</span>,
          ‘turn the mind straight on,’ ‘be bent on battle,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 13.135</span></i>, cf. <i><span class="en">Il. 11.95</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
